1 comp lained of shall have the right to file an answer and to appear
2 and give testimony at the time and place fixed in the complaint. In
3 the discretion of the Board, any other person may be allowed to
4 intervene in such proceeding set the matter for hearing, take
5 evidence, and decide the questions presented.
6 C. If upon the preponderance of the testimony taken the Board
7 shall be of the opinion that the person named in the complaint has
8 engaged in or is engaging in any such unfair labor practice, then
9 the Board shall state its findings of fact and shall issue and cause
10 to be served on such person an order requiring such person to cease
11 and desist from such unfair labor practice. Such order may further
12 require such person to make reports from time to time showing the
13 extent to which it has complied with the order. If upon the
14 preponderance of the testimony taken the Board shall not be of the
15 opinion that the person served in the complaint has engaged in or is
16 engaging in any such unfair labor practice, then the Board shall
17 state its findings of fact and shall issue an order dismissing the
18 complaint.
19 D. The Board, or any interested party, shall have the power to
20 petition the district court, wherein the unfair labor practice in
21 question occurred, for the enforcement of such order and for
22 appropriate temporary relief of restraining order.
